WASHINGTON (WUSA9) -- The Washington Wizards plan on honoring their Baltimore roots during six home games this season by wearing their "Baltimore Pride" throwback jerseys, celebrating the franchise's days in Charm City as the Baltimore Bullets. 
The Wizards took to Twitter to announce the new jerseys. OFFICIAL: #Wizards to wear Baltimore pride jerseys this season http://t.co/r8YrsUjbrt pic.twitter.com/iN8pgu7aez â€” Washington Wizards (@WashWizards) September 30, 2015 
Washington will debut the Baltimore throwbacks against the Charlotte Hornets on December 19 at the Verizon Center.
